@pram, @henningSaulCM, @pacphi Thanks for flagging this bug. I've reproduced the issue - the SpringAI API lacks a reactive version of `ToolCallback`.

I've created a workaround for `AsyncMcpToolCallback` and `AsyncMcpToolcallbackProvider` using @pacphi's approach: https://github.com/tzolov/spring-ai/pull/new/fix-2341

The patch fixes https://github.com/pram/mcp-async-example (@pram: remove mcp-bom as spring-ai handles versioning).

@chemicL: Can't we implement  a better solution around the `Schedulers.boundedElastic()`?
